---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Cookie Policy | HPSC"
	description="Learn about how the Home Performance Stakeholder Council uses cookies and similar technologies on our website."
	keywords="cookie policy, cookies, tracking, web analytics, HPSC"
	breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Cookie Policy', href: '/cookies' }]}
>
	<div class="w-full">
		<!-- Header -->
		<div class="mb-12">
			<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Cookie Policy</h1>
			<p class="text-lg text-gray-600">Last Updated: January 2025</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Content -->
		<div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 md:p-12 prose prose-lg max-w-none">
			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">What Are Cookies?</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Cookies are small text files that are placed on your computer or mobile device when you
					visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently and provide
					information to website owners. Cookies help websites remember information about your
					visit, which can make your next visit easier and the site more useful to you.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">How We Use Cookies</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					The Home Performance Stakeholder Council (HPSC) uses cookies and similar technologies to:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>Ensure the proper functioning of our website</li>
					<li>Remember your preferences and settings</li>
					<li>Analyze website traffic and usage patterns</li>
					<li>Improve website performance and user experience</li>
					<li>Provide personalized content and features</li>
					<li>Measure the effectiveness of our communications</li>
					<li>Prevent fraud and enhance security</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Types of Cookies We Use</h2>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">1. Essential Cookies</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					These cookies are necessary for the website to function properly and cannot be disabled.
					They include:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>
						<strong>Session cookies:</strong> Maintain your session and enable basic functionality
					</li>
					<li><strong>Security cookies:</strong> Authenticate users and prevent fraudulent use</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Load balancing cookies:</strong> Distribute website traffic across servers
					</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">2. Functional Cookies</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					These cookies enable enhanced functionality and personalization:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>
						<strong>Preference cookies:</strong> Remember your settings (language, region, etc.)
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>User interface cookies:</strong> Remember your selected options and customizations
					</li>
					<li><strong>Form cookies:</strong> Remember information you've entered in forms</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">3. Analytics Cookies</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our website:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>
						<strong>Google Analytics:</strong> Tracks page views, user behavior, and traffic sources
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Performance cookies:</strong> Collect information about how you use our website
					</li>
					<li><strong>Error reporting:</strong> Help us identify and fix technical issues</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Analytics cookies collect data in an aggregated and anonymized form. They do not identify
					you personally.
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">4. Marketing Cookies</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					These cookies track your online activity to help us deliver relevant advertising:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>
						<strong>Advertising cookies:</strong> Used to deliver relevant ads based on your interests
					</li>
					<li><strong>Social media cookies:</strong> Enable sharing content on social platforms</li>
					<li><strong>Retargeting cookies:</strong> Show you relevant ads on other websites</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Third-Party Cookies</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Some cookies on our website are placed by third-party services. These may include:
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Google Analytics</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					We use Google Analytics to understand how visitors use our site. Google Analytics sets
					cookies to collect information in an anonymous form, including:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>Number of visitors to the site</li>
					<li>Pages visited and time spent on each page</li>
					<li>Geographic location (country and city level)</li>
					<li>Device type and browser information</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					For more information about Google Analytics cookies, visit:
					<a
						href="https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/collection/analyticsjs/cookie-usage"
						class="text-primary hover:underline"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer"
					>
						Google Analytics Cookie Usage
					</a>
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Social Media Platforms</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					We may use social media plugins (Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn, etc.) that may set cookies
					when you interact with them or share content.
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Cloudflare</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					We use Cloudflare for security and performance optimization. Cloudflare may set cookies
					to:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>Identify trusted web traffic</li>
					<li>Provide bot management and security features</li>
					<li>Support Turnstile (CAPTCHA alternative) verification</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Cookie Duration</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Cookies may be stored on your device for different periods:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li><strong>Session cookies:</strong> Deleted when you close your browser</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Persistent cookies:</strong> Remain on your device for a set period (days, months,
						or years) or until manually deleted
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Managing Your Cookie Preferences</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					You have several options to control and manage cookies:
				</p>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Browser Settings</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings. You can:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>View what cookies are stored and delete them individually</li>
					<li>Block third-party cookies</li>
					<li>Block all cookies from specific websites</li>
					<li>Block all cookies from being set</li>
					<li>Delete all cookies when you close your browser</li>
				</ul>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					To learn how to manage cookies in your browser, visit:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647"
							class="text-primary hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Chrome</a
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/cookies-information-websites-store-on-your-computer"
							class="text-primary hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">Mozilla Firefox</a
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-sfri11471/mac"
							class="text-primary hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">Safari</a
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09"
							class="text-primary hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">Microsoft Edge</a
						>
					</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Opt-Out Tools</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					You can opt out of certain analytics and advertising cookies:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout"
							class="text-primary hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://optout.networkadvertising.org/"
							class="text-primary hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">Network Advertising Initiative Opt-out</a
						>
					</li>
					<li>
						<a
							href="https://optout.aboutads.info/"
							class="text-primary hover:underline"
							target="_blank"
							rel="noopener noreferrer">Digital Advertising Alliance Opt-out</a
						>
					</li>
				</ul>

				<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Do Not Track</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Some browsers have a "Do Not Track" feature that signals to websites that you don't want
					your online activity tracked. Currently, there is no industry standard for how to respond
					to Do Not Track signals, but we respect your privacy preferences.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Impact of Disabling Cookies</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					Please note that if you disable or block cookies:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>Some parts of our website may not function properly</li>
					<li>Your user experience may be degraded</li>
					<li>You may not be able to access certain features or services</li>
					<li>We may not be able to remember your preferences</li>
					<li>You may need to re-enter information on subsequent visits</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Other Tracking Technologies</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					In addition to cookies, we may use other tracking technologies:
				</p>
				<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
					<li>
						<strong>Web beacons:</strong> Small graphic images used to track page views and user behavior
					</li>
					<li><strong>Local storage:</strong> Browser storage used to save data locally</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Session storage:</strong> Temporary storage that clears when the browser is closed
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Pixel tags:</strong> Transparent images used in emails to track opens and clicks
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Updates to This Policy</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or
					legal requirements. We will notify you of any material changes by updating the "Last
					Updated" date at the top of this policy. We encourage you to review this policy
					periodically.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="mb-8">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Your Consent</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					By using our website, you consent to our use of cookies as described in this Cookie
					Policy. For information about how we use your personal data, please see our
					<a href="/privacy" class="text-primary hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
				<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					If you have questions about our use of cookies or this Cookie Policy, please contact us:
				</p>
				<div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
					<p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold mb-2">Home Performance Stakeholder Council</p>
					<p class="text-gray-700 mb-1">
						Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@homeperformance.ca" class="text-primary hover:underline"
							>privacy@homeperformance.ca</a
						>
					</p>
					<p class="text-gray-700 mb-1">Phone: 1-800-123-4567</p>
					<p class="text-gray-700">Address: Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada</p>
				</div>
			</section>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
